Art. 8. The Quasi Trial is performed at
one Sitting or if more be necessary at divers sittings:
but unless for special and extraordinary reason as-
-signed, it is gone through at one sitting, unless
the whole time employable at that one Sitting
has been consumed before the suit has thus been
rendered ripe for definitive decrees.
Art. 9. At this recapitulatory examination
no evidence is receivable, that was not exhibited
in the course of the original examination.
Art. 10. At this Quasi Trial may be re-
-argued and reconsidered or for the first time ar-
gued and considered, the question of law.
